      <description>&lt;p&gt;Some things I think are worth sharing.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.scientificamerican.com/article/silent-skies-billions-of-north-american-birds-have-vanished/&#34;&gt;Scientific American&lt;/a&gt;: North American bird populations have declined 29% since 1970.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.npr.org/sections/krulwich/2014/02/05/257046530/big-fish-stories-getting-littler&#34;&gt;NPR&lt;/a&gt;: As recently as 1960, fish used to be huge.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://greenyourlab.org&#34;&gt;Green Your Lab&lt;/a&gt;: Good people working on sustainable science.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://prod.sandia.gov/techlib/access-control.cgi/1992/921382.pdf&#34;&gt;WIPP&lt;/a&gt;: How to warn people 10000 years from now about radioactive waste.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://arnavsood.com/cabinet/Jacobson-1972.pdf&#34;&gt;Sylvia Jacobson&lt;/a&gt;: Was confined to a skyjacked plane for a week, and wrote a paper about it.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://kenliu.name/stories/state-change/&#34;&gt;Ken Liu&lt;/a&gt;: State Change (short story).&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.thisamericanlife.org/513/129-cars&#34;&gt;129 Cars&lt;/a&gt;: This American Life (WBEZ Chicago) spends a month at a car dealership.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://theglassroom.org&#34;&gt;The Glass Room&lt;/a&gt;: A digital art exhibit by Mozilla, focused on examining issues of data and privacy.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://panopticlick.eff.org&#34;&gt;Panopticlick&lt;/a&gt;: An EFF tool that lets you see how &amp;ldquo;unique&amp;rdquo; your browser&amp;rsquo;s fingerprint is.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.torproject.org&#34;&gt;Tor&lt;/a&gt;: An easy-to-use version of Firefox that effectively anonymizes your internet traffic.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://writing.kemitchell.com/2016/09/21/MIT-License-Line-by-Line.html&#34;&gt;The MIT License, Line by Line&lt;/a&gt;: &lt;a href=&#34;https://writing.kemitchell.com&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;/dev/lawyer&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/a&gt; does a close-reading of the common MIT License.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://www.inquiringmind.com/article/1901_7_lasn_1-cleaning-up-the-mental-environment-culture-jamming-with-kalle-lasn/&#34;&gt;Kalle Lasn&lt;/a&gt;: &amp;ldquo;Cleaning Up the Mental Environment.&amp;rdquo; Lasn is the founder/publisher of Vancouver-based &lt;em&gt;Adbusters.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://giorgiocalderolla.com/wipr.html&#34;&gt;Wipr&lt;/a&gt;: Highly effective macOS adblocker. I use this.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://gather.town&#34;&gt;Gather.Town&lt;/a&gt;: 8bit online spaces. I invested in this.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
